ohn Webster settled in Ipswich, MA, in 1635; another John Webster (died 1661), ancestor of the lexicographer Noah Webster, emigrated to Cambridge, MA, <i>c.</i> 1631 and later became one of the founders of the colony of CT, of which he was appointed governor in 1656. Daniel Webster (1782–1852), politician and orator, was born in Salisbury, NH, a descendant of Thomas Webster, a prominent 17th-century citizen of Ipswich, MA, whose family had settled there around 1635, while he was still a child."]},{"name":"Web","meanings":["English: variant of   Webb  ."]},{"name":"Webber","meanings":["English (Devon and Somerset): occupational name for a weaver, from Middle English <i>webber</i>, an agent derivative of   Webb  .","Americanized form of German and Jewish (Ashkenazic)   Weber   ‘weaver’."]},{"name":"Webbe","meanings":["English: variant of   Webb  ."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>Maria</i> via Old Welsh <i>Meir</i>.  See  <b>Mary</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mary Webb was born in 1505, in Kent, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 2 sons with William David Atkyns. She died in 1526, in her hometown, at the age of 21."},"et":{"1505–1526":"1505–1526","1500–1540":"1500–1540","1525–1565":"1525–1565","1530–1584":"1530–1584","1525":"1525","1500":"1500","1565":"1565","1530":"1530","1584":"1584","1540":"1540","1505":"1505","1526":"1526","Lyford, Berkshire, England":"Lyford, Berkshire, England","Kent, England":"Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1505–1526":"1505–1526","1500–1540":"1500–1540","1525–1565":"1525–1565","1530–1584":"1530–1584","1525":"1525","1500":"1500","1565":"1565","1530":"1530","1584":"1584","1540":"1540","1505":"1505","1526":"1526","Lyford, Berkshire, England":"Lyford, Berkshire, England","Kent, England":"Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1505–1526":"1505–1526","1500–1540":"1500–1540","1525–1565":"1525–1